Brazil to Extend 6% Tax on Foreign Loans of Up to Two Years, Mantega Says

-- B y   A n d r e   S o l i a n i
-- 
2011-04-06T21:48:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/brazil-to-extend-6-tax-on-foreign-loans-of-up-to-two-years-mantega-says.html
Brazil  will extend a 6 percent tax
on foreign loans maturing in up to two years, Finance Minister
 Guido Mantega  told reporters in Brasilia.  Brazil currently applies the tax to foreign loans maturing
in less than 360 days.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andre Soliani in Brasilia at 
 asoliani@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  